data.description: This charming and updated 4-bedroom Village home from the early 1900's located in downtown Lake Orion offers a unique blend of historical character and modern living. The house, steeped in the history of the area, boasts distinctive architectural features that add to its charm. The wrap-around porch is not only a functional outdoor space but also a nostalgic nod to the past, providing a perfect spot to relax and enjoy the views of the lake. This feature can become a focal point for social gatherings, providing an inviting space for family and friends.  The fenced backyard adds an element of privacy and security, creating a safe haven for recreation or quiet moments.  Spacious bedrooms allow ample space for a family or guests. This open floor plan  offers a Living Room featuring hardwood floors, Library (parlor) with gas fireplace and French doors.  Updated kitchen with Shaker Cabinetry, Center Island, Quartz counters, and a quaint coffee station. Spacious Dining room situated conveniently in the center of the house is the hub of activity, an efficient use of space, and enhances the ambiance of the entire first floor - allowing natural light in from all angles.  Proximity to local amenities, shops, and community events can enhance the overall living experience. The convenience of being in the heart of the town allows for easy access to the vibrant community life while providing a serene retreat with views of the lake. Private Beach and Boat access on All Sport's Lake Orion.
